The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Krishnagar, Sept. 6: Police today arrested the headmaster of a private school in Nadia for illegally storing thousands of books meant for the Sarva Shiksha Abhiyan.

 Basudeb Karmakar was arrested when he was burning the books after coming to know of the police raid. The books were meant to be distributed free to students. 

 Calcutta: A modified tax system, called the goods and services tax, will replace VAT from April 2010, finance minister Asim Dasgupta said on Thursday.




